metadata:

hadiths[34]{hadithnumber,arabic,bengali,english,french,indonesian,russian,urdu,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
{"hadithnumber": "1052", "arabic": "[1052] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ یَزِیدَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ قُسَیْطٍ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْن", "bengali": "", "english": "ahya related to me from Malik that Nafi said, \"I was at al-Juruf (near Madina) and threw a stone at two birds, and hit them. One of them died, and Abdullah ibn Umar threw it away, and then went to slaughter the other one with an adze. It died before he could slaughter it, so Abdullah threw that one away as well", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سیدہ عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا زوجہ رسول اللہ ﷺ سے روایت ہے کہ یقیناً رسول اللہ ﷺ نے حکم فرمایا کہ مردار ک", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 1", "international_number": "1052", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1053", "arabic": "[1053] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ زَیْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ رَجُلٍ مِنْ بَنِی ضَمْرَۃَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard that al-Qasim ibn Muhammad disapproved of eating game that had been killed with throwing sticks and by clay pellets", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "بنوضمرہ کے ایک شخص اپنے والد سے روایت کرتے ہیں کہ رسول اللہ ﷺ سے عقیقے کے بارے میں پوچھا گیا تو آپ ﷺ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Daif'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 2", "international_number": "1053", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1054", "arabic": "[1054] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ جَعْفَرِ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ، عَنْ أَبِیہِ أَ نَّہُ قَالَ : وَزَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Abd ar-Rahman ibn Abi Sasaca that he had heard that Amr ibn al-Jamuh al-Ansari and Abdullah ibn Umar al-Ansari, both of the tribe of Banu Salami, had their grave uncovered by a flood. Their grave was part of what was left after the flood. They were in the same grave, and they were among those martyred at Uhud. They were dug up so that they might be moved. They were found unchanged. It was as if they had died only the day before. One of them had been wounded, and he had put his hand over his wound and had been buried like that. His hand was pulled away from his wound and released, and it returned to where it had been. It was forty-six years between Uhud and the day they were dug up.   Malik said, \"There is no harm in burying two or three men in the same grave due to necessity. The oldest one is put next to the qibla.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "جعفر بن محمد رحمہ اللہ ( المعروف جعفر صادق ) اپنے والد ( محمد المعروف باقر رحمہ اللہ ) سے روایت کرتے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Daif'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 3", "international_number": "1054", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1055", "arabic": "[1055] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ رَبِیعَۃَ بْنِ أبِی عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that Rabia ibn Abi Abd ar-Rahman said, \"Property was sent to Abu Bakr as-Siddiq from Bahrayn. He said, 'If someone had a promise or a pledge with the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, let him come to me.' So Jabir ibn Abdullah came to him, and he gave him three times as much of it as would fill both hands.''", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "محمد ( باقر رحمہ اللہ ) بن علی ( زین العابدین رحمہ اللہ ) بن حسین رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، انھوں نے ک", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 4", "international_number": "1055", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1056", "arabic": "[1056] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ : أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللّٰہِ بْنَ عُمَرَ لَمْ یَکُن", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he heard Nafi say that Abdullah ibn Umar said, \"Whether it eats from it or not", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "نافع رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ کے گھر والوں میں سے کوئی بھی ان", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 5", "international_number": "1056", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1057", "arabic": "[1057] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ رَبِیعَۃَ بْنِ أبِی عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from   Abdullah ibn Abi Bakr that his paternal aunt related that her grandmother made a vow to walk to the Quba mosque. She died, and did not fulfill it, so Abdullah ibn Abbas asked her daughter to walk for her.   Yahya said that he had heard Malik say, \"No one walks for anyone else.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "محمد بن ابراہیم بن حارث تیمی رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، کہتے ہیں کہ میں نے اپنے والد ( ابراہیم بن حارث", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 6", "international_number": "1057", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1058", "arabic": "[1058] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ : أَ نَّہُ عُقَّ عَنْ حَسَنٍ وَحُسَیْنٍ ابْنَی", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that Abdullah ibn Abi Habiba said, \"I said to a man, when I was young, 'A man who only says that he must walk to the House of Allah and does not say that he has vowed to walk, does not have to walk.' A man said, 'Shall I give you this small cucumber?' and he had a small cucumber in his hand and you will say, 'I must walk to the house of Allah?' I said, 'Yes' and I said it, for at that time I was still immature. Then, when I came of age, some one said to me that I had to fulfill my vow. I went and asked Said ibn al- Musayyab about it, and he said to me, 'You must walk.' So I walked.\"   Malik said, \"That is the custom among us.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو خبر پہنچی کہ حضرت علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ کے دونوں کے بیٹوں حضرت حسن رضی", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 7", "international_number": "1058", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1059", "arabic": "[1059] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ ہِشَامِ بْنِ عُرْوَۃَ : أَنَّ أَبَاہُ عُرْوَۃَ بْنَ الزُّبَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Zayd ibn Aslam that Sad al- Jari, the mawla of Umar ibn al-Khattab asked Abdullah ibn Umar about fish which had killed each other or which had died from severe cold . He said, \"There is no harm in eating them.'' Sad said,' 'I then asked Abdullah ibn Amr ibn al As and he said the same", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ہشام بن عروہ رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ ان کے والد عروہ بن زبیر رحمہ اللہ اپنے بیٹوں اور بیٹیوں کی طرف", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 8", "international_number": "1059", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1060", "arabic": "[1060] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ الْحَارِثِ، عَنْ عُبَیْدِ بْنِ فَیْرُوزٍ،", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Abu'z-Zinad from Abu Salama ibn Abd ar-Rahman from Abu Hurayra and Zayd ibn Thabit that they saw no harm in eating what was cast up by the sea", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت براء بن عازب رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک رسول اللہ ﷺ سے سوال کیا گیا کہ کن قربانیوں سے بچ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 9", "international_number": "1060", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1061", "arabic": "[1061] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ : أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللّٰہِ بْنَ عُمَرَ کَانَ یَتَّقِی مِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Abu'z-Zinad from Abu Salama ibn Abd ar-Rahman that some people from al-Jar came to Marwan ibn al- Hakam and asked him about eating what was cast up by the sea. He said, \"There is no harm in eating it.\" Marwan said, \"Go to Zayd ibn Thabit and Abu Hurayra and ask them about it, then come to me and tell me what they say.\" They went to them and asked them, and they both said, \"There is no harm in eating it \" They returned to Marwan and told him. Marwan said, \"I told you.\" Malik said that there was no harm in eating fish caught by magians, because the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"In the sea's water is purity, and that which is dead in it is halal. \" Malik said, \"If it is eaten when it is dead, there is no harm in who catches it", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "نافع رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ ان قربانیوں اور ہدی کے اونٹوں سے بچتے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 10", "international_number": "1061", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1062", "arabic": "[1062] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ یَحْیَی بْنِ سَعِیدٍ، عَنْ بُشَیْرِ بْنِ یَسَارٍ : أَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Ibn Shibab from Abu Idris al- Khawlani from Abu Tha~laba al-Khushani that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It is haram to eat animals with fangs", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "بشیر بن یسار رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک حضرت ابوبردہ بن نیار رضی اللہ عنہ نے اپنی قربانی ذبح کر", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Shadh'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 11", "international_number": "1062", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1063", "arabic": "[1063] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ یَحْیَی بْنِ سَعِیدٍ، عَنْ عَبَّادِ بْنِ تَمِیمٍ، أَنَّ عُوَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Ismail ibn Abi Hakim from Abiyda ibn Sufyan al-Hadrami from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Eating animals with fangs is haram. \" Malik said, \"This is the custom among us", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عباد بن تمیم رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک حضرت عویمر بن اشقر رضی اللہ عنہ نے عیدالاضحی کے دن صبح (", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 12", "international_number": "1063", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1064", "arabic": "[1064] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ : أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللّٰہِ بْنَ عُمَرَ ضَحَّی مَر", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that the best of what he had heard about horses, mules, and donkeys was that they were not eaten because Allah, the Blessed, the Exalted,said, \"And horses, and mules and asses, for you to ride, and as an adornment. \" (Sura 16 ayat 8) . He said, may He be Blessed and Exalted, \"In cattle, some of them you ride, and some of them you eat.\" (Sura 6 ayat 79). He said, the Blessed, the Exalted, \"Mention Allah's name over what He has provided you of cattle, and eat of them and feed the beggar (al-qani) and the suppliant (al-mutarr). (Sura 22 ayat 34). Malik said \"Allah mentioned horses, mules, and donkeys for riding and adornment, and He mentioned cattle for riding and eating.\" Malik said, \"Al-qani also means the poor.\" Yahya related to me from Malik from Ibn Shihab from Ubaydullah ibn Abdullah ibn Utba ibn Masud that Abdullah ibn Abbas said, \"The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, passed by a dead sheep which had been given to a mawla of his wife, Maimuna. He said, ' Aren't you going to use its skin?' They said, 'Messenger of Allah, but it is carrion. 'The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, 'Only eating it is haram", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "نافع رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ نے ایک بار مدینہ میں قربانی کی", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 13", "international_number": "1064", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1065", "arabic": "[1065] حَدَّثَنِی یَحْیَی، عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ أبِی الزُّبَیْرِ الْمَکِّیِّ عَنْ جَابِرِ بْنِ عَبْدِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from Ibn Wala al-Misri from Abdullah ibn Abbas that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"A skin when it is tanned is pure", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ سلمی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک رسول اللہ ﷺ نے ( ایک سال ) قربانیوں کے گ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 14", "international_number": "1065", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1066", "arabic": "[1066] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ أبِی بَکْرٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ وَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Yazid ibn Abdullah ibn Qusayt from Muhammad ibn Abd ar-Rahman ibn Thawban from his mother that A'isha, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, ordered that the skins of carrion be used after they had been tanned", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن ابی بکر بن محمد بن عمرو بن حزم رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، وہ عبداللہ بن واقد رحمہ اللہ سے رو", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 25, Hadith 15", "international_number": "1066", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1098", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي يَحْيَى، عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، أَنَّهُ قَالَ رَمَيْتُ طَائِرَيْنِ بِحَجَرٍ وَأَنَا بِالْجُرْفِ، فَأَصَبْتُهُمَا فَأَمَّا أَحَدُهُمَا فَمَاتَ فَطَرَحَهُ عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ وَأَمَّا الآخَرُ فَذَهَبَ عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ يُذَكِّيهِ بِقَدُومٍ فَمَاتَ قَبْلَ أَنْ يُذَكِّيَهُ فَطَرَحَهُ عَبْدُ اللَّهِ أَيْضًا ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "ahya related to me from Malik that Nafi said, \"I was at al-Juruf (near Madina) and threw a stone at two birds, and hit them. One of them died, and Abdullah ibn Umar threw it away, and then went to slaughter the other one with an adze. It died before he could slaughter it, so Abdullah threw that one away as well.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت خنساء بنت خذام ( یا خدام ) انصاریہ رضی اللہ عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ ان کے والد نے ان کی شادی کر دی", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1098", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1099", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ الْقَاسِمَ بْنَ مُحَمَّدٍ، كَانَ يَكْرَهُ مَا قَتَلَ الْمِعْرَاضُ وَالْبُنْدُقَةُ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard that al-Qasim ibn Muhammad disapproved of eating game that had been killed with throwing sticks and by clay pellets.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوزبیر مکی رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک حضرت عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کے پاس ایک ایسا نکاح ( کا م", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1099", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1100", "arabic": "سَعِيدَ بْنَ الْمُسَيَّبِ، كَانَ يَكْرَهُ أَنْ تُقْتَلَ الإِنْسِيَّةُ، بِمَا يُقْتَلُ بِهِ الصَّيْدُ مِنَ الرَّمْىِ وَأَشْبَاهِهِ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَلاَ أَرَى بَأْسًا بِمَا أَصَابَ الْمِعْرَاضُ إِذَا خَسَقَ وَبَلَغَ الْمَقَاتِلَ أَنْ يُؤْكَلَ قَالَ اللَّهُ تَبَارَكَ وَتَعَالَى ‏{‏يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا لَيَبْلُوَنَّكُمُ اللَّهُ بِشَىْءٍ مِنَ الصَّيْدِ تَنَالُهُ أَيْدِيكُمْ وَرِمَاحُكُمْ ‏}‏ قَالَ فَكُلُّ شَىْءٍ نَالَهُ الإِنْسَانُ بِيَدِهِ أَوْ رُمْحِهِ أَوْ بِشَىْءٍ مِنْ سِلاَحِهِ فَأَنْفَذَهُ وَبَلَغَ مَقَاتِلَهُ فَهُوَ صَيْدٌ كَمَا قَالَ اللَّهُ تَعَالَى", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard that Said ibn al-Musayyab disapproved of killing domestic animals that had become wild by any means that game was slain such as arrows and the like.   Malik said, \"I do not see any harm in eating game which is pierced by a throwing stick in a vital organ.   Allah, the Blessed, the Exalted! said, 'Oh you who believe! Allah will surely try you with something of the game that your hands and spears attain.' \" (Sura 5 ayat 97).   Yahya said, \"Any game that man obtains by his hand or by his spear or by any weapon which pierces it and reaches a vital organ, is acceptable as Allah, the Exalted, has said.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سعید بن مسیب رحمہ اللہ اور سلیمان بن یسار رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک ( عشرہ مبشرہ میں سے ایک حضر", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1100", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1101", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ أَهْلَ الْعِلْمِ يَقُولُونَ إِذَا أَصَابَ الرَّجُلُ الصَّيْدَ فَأَعَانَهُ عَلَيْهِ غَيْرُهُ مِنْ مَاءٍ أَوْ كَلْبٍ غَيْرِ مُعَلَّمٍ لَمْ يُؤْكَلْ ذَلِكَ الصَّيْدُ إِلاَّ أَنْ يَكُونَ سَهْمُ الرَّامِي قَدْ قَتَلَهُ أَوْ بَلَغَ مَقَاتِلَ الصَّيْدِ حَتَّى لاَ يَشُكَّ أَحَدٌ فِي أَنَّهُ هُوَ قَتَلَهُ وَأَنَّهُ لاَ يَكُونُ لِلصَّيْدِ حَيَاةٌ بَعْدَهُ ‏.‏ قَالَ وَسَمِعْتُ مَالِكًا يَقُولُ لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِ الصَّيْدِ - وَإِنْ غَابَ عَنْكَ مَصْرَعُهُ - إِذَا وَجَدْتَ بِهِ أَثَرًا مِنْ كَلْبِكَ أَوْ كَانَ بِهِ سَهْمُكَ مَا لَمْ يَبِتْ فَإِذَا بَاتَ فَإِنَّهُ يُكْرَهُ أَكْلُهُ ‏.", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard the people of knowledge say that when a man hit game and something else might have contributed to death, like water or an untrained dog, that game was not to be eaten unless it was beyond doubt that it was the arrow of the hunter that had killed it by reaching a vital organ, so that it did not have any life after that.   Yahya said that he heard Malik say that there was no harm in eating game when you did not see it die if you found the mark of your dog on it or your arrow in it as long as it had not remained overnight. If it had remained overnight, then it was disapproved of to eat it.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ حضرت عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ اور حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1101", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1102", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي يَحْيَى، عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، أَنَّهُ كَانَ يَقُولُ فِي الْكَلْبِ الْمُعَلَّمِ كُلْ مَا أَمْسَكَ عَلَيْكَ إِنْ قَتَلَ وَإِنْ لَمْ يَقْتُلْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Nafi that Abdullah ibn Umar said about a trained dog, \"Eat whatever it catches for you whether it eats from it or not.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سعید بن مسیب رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، وہ کہا کرتے تھے کہ آزاد عورت پر لونڈی سے نکاح نہ کیا جائے ، الا", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1102", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1103", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَمَّنْ سَمِعَ نَافِعًا، يَقُولُ قَالَ عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ وَإِنْ أَكَلَ وَإِنْ لَمْ يَأْكُلْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he heard Nafi say that Abdullah ibn Umar said, \"Whether it eats from it or not.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت زید بن ثابت رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک وہ اس شخص کے متعلق فرمایا کرتے تھے جو لونڈی کو تی", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1103", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1104", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ عَنْ سَعْدِ بْنِ أَبِي وَقَّاصٍ، أَنَّهُ سُئِلَ عَنِ الْكَلْبِ الْمُعَلَّمِ، إِذَا قَتَلَ الصَّيْدَ فَقَالَ سَعْدٌ كُلْ وَإِنْ لَمْ تَبْقَ إِلاَّ بِضْعَةٌ وَاحِدَةٌ ‏.‏ وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ عَنْ سَعْدِ بْنِ أَبِي وَقَّاصٍ، أَنَّهُ سُئِلَ عَنِ الْكَلْبِ الْمُعَلَّمِ، إِذَا قَتَلَ الصَّيْدَ فَقَالَ سَعْدٌ كُلْ وَإِنْ لَمْ تَبْقَ إِلاَّ بِضْعَةٌ وَاحِدَةٌ ‏.", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard that Sad ibn Abi Waqqas had said, when asked about a trained dog killing game, \"Eat, even if only one piece of it remains.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ سعید بن مسیب رحمہ اللہ اور سلیمان بن یسار رحمہ اللہ سے اس شخص", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1104", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1105", "arabic": ".‏ وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ بَعْضَ أَهْلِ الْعِلْمِ يَقُولُونَ فِي الْبَازِي وَالْعُقَابِ وَالصَّقْرِ وَمَا أَشْبَهَ ذَلِكَ أَنَّهُ إِذَا كَانَ يَفْقَهُ كَمَا تَفْقَهُ الْكِلاَبُ الْمُعَلَّمَةُ فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِ مَا قَتَلَتْ مِمَّا صَادَتْ إِذَا ذُكِرَ اسْمُ اللَّهِ عَلَى إِرْسَالِهَا ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَأَحْسَنُ مَا سَمِعْتُ فِي الَّذِي يَتَخَلَّصُ الصَّيْدَ مِنْ مَخَالِبِ الْبَازِي أَوْ مِنَ الْكَلْبِ ثُمَّ يَتَرَبَّصُ بِهِ فَيَمُوتُ أَنَّهُ لاَ يَحِلُّ أَكْلُهُ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَكَذَلِكَ كُلُّ مَا قُدِرَ عَلَى ذَبْحِهِ وَهُوَ فِي مَخَالِبِ الْبَازِي أَوْ فِي الْكَلْبِ فَيَتْرُكُهُ صَاحِبُهُ وَهُوَ قَادِرٌ عَلَى ذَبْحِهِ حَتَّى يَقْتُلَهُ الْبَازِي أَوِ الْكَلْبُ فَإِنَّهُ لاَ يَحِلُّ أَكْلُهُ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَكَذَلِكَ الَّذِي يَرْمِي الصَّيْدَ فَيَنَالُهُ وَهُوَ حَىٌّ فَيُفَرِّطُ فِي ذَبْحِهِ حَتَّى يَمُوتَ فَإِنَّهُ لاَ يَحِلُّ أَكْلُهُ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ الأَمْرُ الْمُجْتَمَعُ عَلَيْهِ عِنْدَنَا أَنَّ الْمُسْلِمَ إِذَا أَرْسَلَ كَلْبَ الْمَجُوسِيِّ الضَّارِيَ فَصَادَ أَوْ قَتَلَ إِنَّهُ إِذَا كَانَ مُعَلَّمًا فَأَكْلُ ذَلِكَ الصَّيْدِ حَلاَلٌ لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ وَإِنْ لَمْ يُذَكِّهِ الْمُسْلِمُ وَإِنَّمَا مَثَلُ ذَلِكَ مَثَلُ الْمُسْلِمِ يَذْبَحُ بِشَفْرَةِ الْمَجُوسِيِّ أَوْ يَرْمِي بِقَوْسِهِ أَوْ بِنَبْلِهِ فَيَقْتُلُ بِهَا فَصَيْدُهُ ذَلِكَ وَذَبِيحَتُهُ حَلاَلٌ لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِهِ وَإِذَا أَرْسَلَ الْمَجُوسِيُّ كَلْبَ الْمُسْلِمِ الضَّارِيَ عَلَى صَيْدٍ فَأَخَذَهُ فَإِنَّهُ لاَ يُؤْكَلُ ذَلِكَ الصَّيْدُ إِلاَّ أَنْ يُذَكَّى  وَإِنَّمَا مَثَلُ ذَلِكَ مَثَلُ قَوْسِ الْمُسْلِمِ وَنَبْلِهِ يَأْخُذُهَا الْمَجُوسِيُّ فَيَرْمِي بِهَا الصَّيْدَ فَيَقْتُلُهُ وَبِمَنْزِلَةِ شَفْرَةِ الْمُسْلِمِ يَذْبَحُ بِهَا الْمَجُوسِيُّ فَلاَ يَحِلُّ أَكْلُ شَىْءٍ مِنْ ذَلِكَ ‏.", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that he had heard some of the people of knowledge say that when falcons, eagles, and hawks and their like, understood as trained dogs understood, there was no harm in eating what they had killed in the course of hunting, if the name of Allah had been mentioned when they were sent out.   Malik said, \"The best of what I have heard about retrieving game from the falcon's talons or from the dog's fangs and then waiting until it dies, is that it is not halal to eat it.\"   Malik said, \"The same applies to anything which could have been slaughtered by the hunter when it was in the talons of the falcon or the fangs of the dog. If the hunter leaves it until the falcon or dog has killed it, it is not halal to eat it either\". He continued, \"The same thing applies to any game hit by a hunter and caught while still alive, which he neglects to slaughter before it dies.\"   Malik said, \"It is generally agreed among us that it is halal to eat the game that a hunting-dog belonging to magians hunts or kills, if it is sent out by a muslim and the animal is trained. There is no harm in it even if the muslim does not actually slaughter it.   It is the same as a muslim using a magian's knife to slaughter with or using his bow and arrows to shoot and kill with. The game he shot and the animal he slaughters are halal. There is no harm in eating them. If a magian sends out a muslim's hunting dog for game, and it catches it, the game is not to be eaten unless it is slaughtered by a muslim. That is like a magian using a muslim's bow and arrow to hunt game with, or like his using a muslim's knife to slaughter with. It is not halal to eat anything killed like that.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ نے ابن شہاب رحمہ اللہ اس شخص کے متعلق سوال کیا جس کے نکاح میں لونڈی تھی جو کسی ا", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1105", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1106", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي يَحْيَى، عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، أَنَّ عَبْدَ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنَ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، سَأَلَ عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ عُمَرَ عَمَّا لَفَظَ الْبَحْرُ فَنَهَاهُ عَنْ أَكْلِهِ، ‏.‏ قَالَ نَافِعٌ ثُمَّ انْقَلَبَ عَبْدُ اللَّهِ فَدَعَا بِالْمُصْحَفِ فَقَرَأَ ‏{‏أُحِلَّ لَكُمْ صَيْدُ الْبَحْرِ وَطَعَامُهُ‏}‏ قَالَ نَافِعٌ فَأَرْسَلَنِي عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ إِلَى عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ إِنَّهُ لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِهِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Nafi that Abd ar-Rahman ibn Abi Hurayra asked Abdullah ibn Umar about eating what was cast up by the sea and he forbade him to eat it. Then Abdullah turned and asked for a Qur'an, and read, \"The game of the sea and its flesh are halal for you.\" Nafi added, \"Abdullah ibn Umar sent me to Abdar-Rahman Ibn Abi Hurayra to say that there was no harm in eating it.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبیداللہ بن عبداللہ بن عتبہ رحمہ اللہ اپنے والد عبداللہ بن عتبہ بن مسعود رحمہ اللہ سے روایت کرتے ہیں", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1106", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1107", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ سَعْدٍ الْجَارِيِّ، مَوْلَى عُمَرَ بْنِ الْخَطَّابِ أَنَّهُ قَالَ سَأَلْتُ عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ عُمَرَ عَنِ الْحِيتَانِ، يَقْتُلُ بَعْضُهَا بَعْضًا أَوْ تَمُوتُ صَرَدًا فَقَالَ لَيْسَ بِهَا بَأْسٌ ‏.‏ قَالَ سَعْدٌ ثُمَّ سَأَلْتُ عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ عَمْرِو بْنِ الْعَاصِ فَقَالَ مِثْلَ ذَلِكَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Zayd ibn Aslam that Sad al- Jari, the mawla of Umar ibn al-Khattab asked Abdullah ibn Umar about fish which had killed each other or which had died from severe cold . He said, \"There is no harm in eating them.'' Sad said,' 'I then asked Abdullah ibn Amr ibn al As and he said the same.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "قبیصہ بن ذُؤیب رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، ایک شخص نے حضرت عثمان بن عفان رضی اللہ عنہ سے دو بہنوں کے مت", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1107", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1108", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنْ أَبِي سَلَمَةَ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، وَزَيْدِ بْنِ ثَابِتٍ، أَنَّهُمَا كَانَا لاَ يَرَيَانِ بِمَا لَفَظَ الْبَحْرُ بَأْسًا ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Abu'z-Zinad from Abu Salama ibn Abd ar-Rahman from Abu Hurayra and Zayd ibn Thabit that they saw no harm in eating what was cast up by the sea.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو حضرت زُبیر بن عوام رضی اللہ عنہ سے بھی اسی طرح کی روایت پہنچی تھی ۔", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1108", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1109", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنْ أَبِي سَلَمَةَ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، أَنَّ نَاسًا، مِنْ أَهْلِ الْجَارِ قَدِمُوا فَسَأَلُوا مَرْوَانَ بْنَ الْحَكَمِ عَمَّا لَفَظَ الْبَحْرُ فَقَالَ لَيْسَ بِهِ بَأْسٌ وَقَالَ اذْهَبُوا إِلَى زَيْدِ بْنِ ثَابِتٍ وَأَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ فَاسْأَلُوهُمَا عَنْ ذَلِكَ ثُمَّ ائْتُونِي فَأَخْبِرُونِي مَاذَا يَقُولاَنِ فَأَتَوْهُمَا فَسَأَلُوهُمَا فَقَالاَ لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ ‏.‏ فَأَتَوْا مَرْوَانَ فَأَخْبَرُوهُ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ مَرْوَانُ قَدْ قُلْتُ لَكُمْ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِ الْحِيتَانِ يَصِيدُهَا الْمَجُوسِيُّ لأَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ فِي الْبَحْرِ ‏ ‏ هُوَ الطَّهُورُ مَاؤُهُ الْحِلُّ مَيْتَتُهُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَإِذَا أُكِلَ ذَلِكَ مَيْتًا فَلاَ يَضُرُّهُ مَنْ صَادَهُ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Abu'z-Zinad from Abu Salama ibn Abd ar-Rahman that some people from al-Jar came to Marwan ibn al- Hakam and asked him about eating what was cast up by the sea. He said, \"There is no harm in eating it.\" Marwan said, \"Go to Zayd ibn Thabit and Abu Hurayra and ask them about it, then come to me and tell me what they say.\" They went to them and asked them, and they both said, \"There is no harm in eating it \" They returned to Marwan and told him. Marwan said, \"I told you.\"    Malik said that there was no harm in eating fish caught by magians, because the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"In the sea's water is purity, and that which is dead in it is halal. \"   Malik said, \"If it is eaten when it is dead, there is no harm in who catches it.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1110", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي يَحْيَى، عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنِ أَبِي إِدْرِيسَ الْخَوْلاَنِيِّ، عَنْ أَبِي ثَعْلَبَةَ الْخُشَنِيِّ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ أَكْلُ كُلِّ ذِي نَابٍ مِنَ السِّبَاعِ حَرَامٌ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Ibn Shibab from Abu Idris al- Khawlani from Abu Tha~laba al-Khushani that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It is haram to eat animals with fangs \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1111", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ إِسْمَاعِيلَ بْنِ أَبِي حَكِيمٍ، عَنْ عَبِيدَةَ بْنِ سُفْيَانَ الْحَضْرَمِيِّ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ أَكْلُ كُلِّ ذِي نَابٍ مِنَ السِّبَاعِ حَرَامٌ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Ismail ibn Abi Hakim from Abiyda ibn Sufyan al-Hadrami from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Eating animals with fangs is haram. \"   Malik said, \"This is the custom among us.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1112", "arabic": "[1112] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ إِبْرَاہِیمَ بْنِ أبِی عَبْلَۃَ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الْمَلِکِ بْنِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that the best of what he had heard about horses, mules, and donkeys was that they were not eaten because Allah, the Blessed, the Exalted,said, \"And horses, and mules and asses, for you to ride, and as an adornment. \" (Sura 16 ayat 8) . He said, may He be Blessed and Exalted, \"In cattle, some of them you ride, and some of them you eat.\" (Sura 6 ayat 79). He said, the Blessed, the Exalted, \"Mention Allah's name over what He has provided you of cattle, and eat of them and feed the beggar (al-qani) and the suppliant (al-mutarr). (Sura 22 ayat 34).   Malik said \"Allah mentioned horses, mules, and donkeys for riding and adornment, and He mentioned cattle for riding and eating.\"   Malik said, \"Al-qani also means the poor.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبدالملک بن مروان رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ انھوں نے اپنے ایک ساتھی کو ایک لونڈی تحفہ میں دی ، پھر ان", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1112", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1113", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي يَحْيَى، عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ عُبَيْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُتْبَةَ بْنِ مَسْعُودٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَبَّاسٍ، أَنَّهُ قَالَ مَرَّ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم بِشَاةٍ مَيِّتَةٍ كَانَ أَعْطَاهَا مَوْلاَةً لِمَيْمُونَةَ زَوْجِ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم فَقَالَ ‏\"‏ أَفَلاَ انْتَفَعْتُمْ بِجِلْدِهَا ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَقَالُوا يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ إِنَّهَا مَيْتَةٌ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ إِنَّمَا حُرِّمَ أَكْلُهَا ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Ibn Shihab from Ubaydullah ibn Abdullah ibn Utba ibn Masud that Abdullah ibn Abbas said, \"The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, passed by a dead sheep which had been given to a mawla of his wife, Maimuna. He said, ' Aren't you going to use its skin?' They said, 'Messenger of Allah, but it is carrion. 'The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, 'Only eating it is haram.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سعید بن مسیب رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، انھوں نے فرمایا کہ ( پانچویں پارے کے ابتدائی الفاظ ) { وَّالْمُ", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1113", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1114", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنِ ابْنِ وَعْلَةَ الْمِصْرِيِّ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَبَّاسٍ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا دُبِغَ الإِهَابُ فَقَدْ طَهُرَ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from Ibn Wala al-Misri from Abdullah ibn Abbas that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"A skin when it is tanned is pure.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1115", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي عَنْ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ يَزِيدَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ قُسَيْطٍ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ ثَوْبَانَ، عَنْ أُمِّهِ، عَنْ عَائِشَةَ، زَوْجِ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم أَمَرَ أَنْ يُسْتَمْتَعَ بِجُلُودِ الْمَيْتَةِ إِذَا دُبِغَتْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik from Yazid ibn Abdullah ibn Qusayt from Muhammad ibn Abd ar-Rahman ibn Thawban from his mother that A'isha, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, ordered that the skins of carrion be used after they had been tanned.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے خیبر کے دن عورتوں کے ساتھ متع", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1115", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
{"hadithnumber": "1116", "arabic": "[1116] وَحَدَّثَنِی عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِہَابٍ، عَنْ عُرْوَۃَ بْنِ الزُّبَیْرِ : أَنَّ خَوْلَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Yahya related to me from Malik that the best of what he had heard about a man who is forced by necessity to eat carrion is that he ate it until he was full and then he took provision from it. If he found something which would enable him to dispense with it, he threw it away.   Malik when asked whether or not a man who had been forced by necessity to eat carrion, should eat it when he also found the fruit, crops or sheep of a people in that place, answered, \"If he thinks that the owners of the fruit, crops, or sheep will believe his necessity so that he will not be deemed a thief and have his hand cut off, then I think that he should eat from whatever he finds that which will remove his hunger but he should not carry any of it away. I prefer that he does that than that he eat carrion. If he fears that he will not be believed, and will be deemed a thief for what he has taken, then I think that it is better for him to eat the carrion, and he has leeway to eat carrion in this respect. Even so, I fear that someone who is not forced by necessity to eat carrion might exceed the limits out of a desire to consume other peoples' property, crops or fruit.\"   Malik said, \"That is the best of what I have heard.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عروہ بن زبیر رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ حضرت خولہ بنت حکیم رضی اللہ عنہا حضرت عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "1116", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Game"}
